<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT - INSTALL - STEERING WHEEL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>STEERING WHEEL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the front wheels in a straight forward position, put the steering wheel on the column
                shaft so the two steering wheel spokes are at 4 o'clock and 8 o'clock.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the steering wheel nut and tighten as specified in the
                <hotlnk document="s05008t_12.xml" xrefid="hl0500801">TORQUE CHART
                    <xref refid="hl0500801"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect wires to horn button cover. Position cover so it fits recess, then install the two
                screws from the underside of the steering wheel into the cover. Tighten until snug.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reconnect battery negative cable.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
